onsortium, 14 October 2008, http://www.w3.org/TR/rdfa-syntax/.</iml:p></iml:li><iml:li id="EARMARKEKAW"><iml:p>Di Iorio, A., Peroni, S., Vitali, F. (2010). Handling markup overlaps using OWL. In Proceedings of the 17th International Conference on Knowledge Engineering and Knowledge Management (EKAW 2010). 11-15 October 2010, Lisbon, Portugal.</iml:p></iml:li><iml:li id="Bibo"><iml:p>D'Arcus, B., Giasson, F. (2009). Bibliographic Ontology Specification. Specification Document, 4 November 2009, http://bibliontology.com/specification.</iml:p></iml:li><iml:li id="FRBR"><iml:p>IFLA Study Group on the Functional Requirements for Bibliographic Records (1998). Functional Requirements for Bibliographic Records (FRBR). Final Report, http://archive.ifla.org/VII/s13/frbr/frbr_current_toc.htm.</iml:p></iml:li></iml:ul></iml:div><iml:div class="footnote"><iml:div id="ftn4"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://usefulinc.com/ns/doap">http://usefulinc.com/ns/doap</iml:a></iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn5"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://vocab.ox.ac.uk/projectfunding/index.rdf">http://vocab.ox.ac.uk/projectfunding/index.rdf</iml:a></iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn6"><iml:p>http://purl.org/spar/fabio</iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn7"><iml:p>Http://purl.org/spar/biro</iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn0"><iml:p>According to <iml:a class="ref" href="RenearTowardsSemantics"/>, <iml:i>markup semantics</iml:i> and (the most commonly known, within the Semantic Web community) <iml:i>semantic markup</iml:i> describe different kinds of semantics. The former is involved when answering the question “what is the meaning of a particular markup element <iml:i>title</iml:i> contained in a document <iml:i>d</iml:i>?”, while the latter relates to the sentence “the resource <iml:i>r</iml:i> has the string “The irreducible complexity of the authorial chain in academic semantic publishing” as title”.</iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn9"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://www.essepuntato.it/2008/12/earmark">http://www.essepuntato.it/2008/12/earmark</iml:a></iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn10"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://www.essepuntato.it/xml2earmark">http://www.essepuntato.it/xml2earmark</iml:a></iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn11"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://earmark.sourceforge.net/">http://earmark.sourceforge.net</iml:a></iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn12"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://purl.org/spar/doco">http://purl.org/spar/doco</iml:a></iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn14"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://purl.org/spar/deo">http://purl.org/spar/deo</iml:a></iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn15"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://purl.org/spar/cito">http://purl.org/spar/cito</iml:a> </iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn16"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://www.essepuntato.it/2011/02/argumentmodel">http://www.essepuntato.it/2011/02/argumentmodel</iml:a> </iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn17"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://open-biomed.sourceforge.net/opmv/opmv-guide.html">http://open-biomed.sourceforge.net/opmv/opmv-guide.html</iml:a> </iml:p></iml:div><iml:div id="ftn19"><iml:p><iml:a href="http://vocab.org/frbr/core">http://vocab.org/frbr/core</iml:a> and <iml:a href="http://purl.org/spar/frbr">http://purl.org/spar/frbr</iml:a> respectively.</iml:p></iml:div></iml:div></iml:body></iml:iml>